# Thread Synchronization and Signal Handling in C with Shared Memory and Bash Script Control

# This is a comprehensive C application that integrates multithreading, signal handling, and shared memory management, alongside a controlling bash script. The challenge is divided into specific requirements to test your proficiency in system programming and script automation.

## one must grant execution permission to launch_app.sh.
- chmod +x  launch_app.sh

## To compile the C application
- make

## To run the c application
- ./main &

## To send SIGINT Signal 
- ctrl + c

## To run control script
- ./launch_app.sh &  
### (Run this in terminal where "&" represent the duration till we want to run.)
